					In places where you would consider using <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.gnu.org/software/mcron/manual/html_node/Crontab-file.html"><code>cron</code></a> to run a program at the lowest time resolution (i.e., 1 minute) (to approximate a server or some other kind of long-running program) the <a rel="nofollow" href="http://libslack.org/daemon/manpages/daemon.1.html"><code>daemon</code></a> command may be a better choice.
